Briefly remark on the plot and what it indicates to you in terms of the experimentThere is a noticeable separation between the control and knockout groups along PC1. The control samples (blue) are positioned more positively along PC1, while the knockout samples (red) are on the more negative side of PC1. This separation could indicate that the knockout mutation has a significant effect on the gene expression profile being studied, as PC1 typically represents the direction of greatest variability.

Differences: The FGSEA results highlight several pathways related to cell motility, signaling, and adhesion, such as "REACTOME_MET_PROMOTES_CELL_MOTILITY", "REACTOME_SYNAPTIC_ADHESION_LIKE_MOLECULES", and "REACTOME_THROMBOXANE_SIGNALLING_THROUGH_TP_RECEPTOR", which are not as prominent in the gene set enrichment analysis.
